WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:04.080
Think twice before plugging your phone into any public USB charging station.

00:04.880 --> 00:09.920
It seems super convenient when your battery is low, but these stations are a major security risk.

00:10.880 --> 00:15.600
Criminals can easily modify them. They can install malicious software.

00:16.560 --> 00:20.320
This trick is called juice jacking. When you connect your phone,

00:20.320 --> 00:22.960
that hidden malware can instantly infect your device.

00:23.920 --> 00:25.920
It can steal all your personal data.

00:26.800 --> 00:30.720
We're talking passwords, photos, banking details, even your identity.

00:31.600 --> 00:36.080
Your phone isn't just getting power, it's making a data connection to an unknown computer.

00:36.960 --> 00:39.440
And that computer might be controlled by hackers.

00:40.400 --> 00:42.880
It's a huge privacy nightmare waiting to happen.

00:43.760 --> 00:49.920
To stay safe, always use your own wall charger plugged into an AC outlet or carry a power bank.

